<br>
The RN saw the bum and still hit him, she left him to die, she offered no aide as she was most likely qualified to do something, she didn't seek out help for the person she hit, instead she made a concious decision to let that person die because she was more worried about crack or sex or whatever it was. She basically committed murder intentionally, not to say she started out that day to kill a homeless person but she possibly could have prevented it once she was alerted to his predicament.<br>
<br>
If this mother saw their child in despair do we really believe she would have left her to die so that she could play a game? There's been no cause to believe she would have even attempted to cover it up. This woman wasn't the spawn of satan she was just like most of us. The difference is she didn't know where to draw the line between her hobby and responsibilities of her life and as it was fate dealt out her punishment for that by taking her daughter.<br>
<br>
Many times I group with stay at home parents who play while their kids run around the house and now and then you get afk kids getting into something, or afk have to see what they are crying about. This could just as easily have happened to any of them it just so happens it happened to this woman that none of us know offhand.<br>
<br>
She did play a large role in her child's death and blame can go on no one other than her unless someone locked that child in the car(still not sure how a three year old got outside of the house unattended let alone inside of what should have been a locked car) but from the evidence provided by the article she did not intentionally kill her child.<br>
<br>
Now for another sad turn of events no one has yet mentioned. This woman has another child who is I believe I read was nine years old. What happens to this child, clearly it can't be left with the mother even if she isn't incarcerated, the mother has said the father has been abusive to her prior to the divorce and had hit her 2 yr old(to what extent it doesn't really say), this child lost his/her sister, the mother may be jailed, the father is abusive. If the family doesn't take them it will be one more child in the system as a result of two people who were not prepared to have children.<br>
<br>
Hopefully people can learn from this, know their priorities and responsibilities, count their blessings it hasn't been their children yet, and very importantly don't have children unless you are absolutely sure you are mentally, physically and financially able to care for them. Its wrong to bring children into this world if you're not fully committed to them and stable enough to rear them. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#242422><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub40.ezboard.com/bthesaryrntavern.showUserPublicProfile?gid=vainne>Vainne</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Night-blind Bard</span><br>  Posts: 2727<br> <font color=#6FB8DD>(8/21/03 10:38 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub40.ezboard.com/fthesaryrntavernthefurnace.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3489.topic&index=28>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: lady</span><hr size=1> When you're playing eq how much supervision do you give a three year old? No, really, I have no idea. My dog sits at my feet or sneaks into the bathroom and eats my clothes....presumably a toddler would do more, could do more.<br>
