This wasn't a one time thing.  This woman obviously was neglectful.  Don't blame it on EQ, and she sure as hell doesn't have a real defense.  <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>She hurts right now, she knows it's her fault, and losing her child will cause more pain than words typed by strangers ever will be able too<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Well, maybe she should have thought about that before NEGLECTING her child?  <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>A 3 year old needs supervision</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->.  1mil to 1 odds this 21 year old she's shacking up with (read the article, boyfriend, not husband) is someone she met online, yet a year ago she was SO opposed to the game.<br>
<br>
It's her fault, period.  Don't try to shift the blame elsewhere, I feel sympathy for the other child having his life torn apart by an obviously screwed up family, and losing a sibling.  I have no sympathy for a woman who would obviously neglect her children in such a fashion.<br>
<br>
Kero<br>
