<br>
I have never had a problem taking a 2 minute break so a group mate could go check on the kids. I've been known to wait much longer, happily, while all manner of parent-type tasks were being completed. Other peoples kids &gt; My Xp. That is how it should be.<br>
<br>
Most EQ'rs that I know that have really small kids have their computers set up in the same area their kids play. Near the TV, the toy box etc. Usually the living room so they can keep an eye on the whereabouts of the youngins. I don't really agree with spending all your time playing EQ if you have small kids, but it's not for me to say how much time in Norrath is too much. I won't parent someone elses children, but for fuckssake, there is a difference between being a neglectful parent and a GROSSLY NEGLIGENT one. Neglectful = &quot;Mommy didnt hug me enough as a child, but I was fed, clothed, and made it to school&quot;. Grossly negligent = Being locked in a car and being dead.<br>
<br>
EQ itself is not the problem, its a symptom. If EQ were non-existant, these parents would play DAOC, or Asherons call, or any of a billion other games out there right now. If it werent an MMORPG it would be a chat room thingy one. If that were outlawed too, it would be just a chatroom. If it werent a chatroom, it would be a bar. If it werent a bar, it would be a guy upstairs in the bedroom. <br>
<br>
I used to be addicted to EQ to the point where I wouldn't leave the house, wouldn't eat, wouldnt pull myself away from the computer to visit the lil necro's room. Id go far too long between showers. Id never answer the phone, told my mother and roomates to screw off.. etc. You bet your ass my cat was well fed and when I heard a loud noise from the other room, or things were suspisciously quiet I would go and investigate. I know my cat is not a child, but in every regard, a child is MORE than my cat, and if I, the stereotypical addict (at the time) could tear myself from the screen for a four footed fluffy companion, then I feel I can go out on a limb here and say that that mother had deeper seeded issues than EQ. Issues that involved not caring where her child was. Issues with being a mother. Issues with life on earth, not life in Norrath.<br>
<br>
EQ is not to blame, no matter what a world that loves to scapegoat corporations and shirk off any personal responsibility tells you. <br>
<br>
Jasminia <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub40.ezboard.com/bthesaryrntavern.showUserPublicProfile?gid=utmostisen>UtmostIsen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><span style='color:pink;'>Tavern Floor Sweeper</span></span><br>  Posts: 21<br> <font color=#6FB8DD>(8/22/03 7:29 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub40.ezboard.com/fthesaryrntavernthefurnace.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3489.topic&index=33>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> crazy</span><hr size=1> For something crazy click on the link in the article, then search that eq widows deal for Christina Cordell.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#242422><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub40.ezboard.com/bthesaryrntavern.showUserPublicProfile?gid=adaari>Adaari</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.division-usa.com/avatar2.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle><span style='color:yellow;'>Tavern Ale Swiller</span></span><br>  Posts: 53<br> <font color=#6FB8DD>(8/23/03 2:53 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub40.ezboard.com/fthesaryrntavernthefurnace.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3489.topic&index=34>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.division-usa.com/avatar2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: crazy</span><hr size=1> Sad that personal responsibility and accountability count for nothing.  It's always the fault of televison, music, video games, and/or computers.  God forbid parents would actually moderate what their children do and watch, and how dare we expect adults to grow up and take care o